.Sh HISTORY
.Fn BN_add ,
.Fn BN_sub ,
.Fn BN_mul ,
.Fn BN_sqr ,
.Fn BN_div ,
.Fn BN_mod ,
.Fn BN_mod_mul ,
.Fn BN_mod_exp ,
and
.Fn BN_gcd
first appeared in SSLeay 0.5.1.
.Fn BN_exp
first appeared in SSLeay 0.9.0.
All these functions have been available since
.Ox 2.4 .
.Pp
The
.Fa ctx
argument to
.Fn BN_mul
was added in SSLeay 0.9.1 and
.Ox 2.6 .
.Pp
.Fn BN_nnmod ,
.Fn BN_mod_add ,
.Fn BN_mod_sub ,
and
.Fn BN_mod_sqr
first appeared in OpenSSL 0.9.7 and have been available since
.Ox 3.2 .
.Sh BUGS
Even if the
.Dv BN_FLG_CONSTTIME
flag is set on
.Fa a
or
.Fa b ,
.Fn BN_gcd
neither fails nor operates in constant time, potentially allowing
timing side-channel attacks.
.Pp
Even if the
.Dv BN_FLG_CONSTTIME
flag is set on
.Fa p ,
if the modulus
.Fa m
is even,
.Fn BN_mod_exp
does not operate in constant time, potentially allowing
timing side-channel attacks.
.Pp
If
.Dv BN_FLG_CONSTTIME
is set on
.Fa p ,
.Fn BN_exp
fails instead of operating in constant time.
